about.description:
DBF is a file format used by databases such dBase, Visual FoxPro, and
FoxBase+. This library reads DBF files and returns the data as native
Python data types for further processing. It is primarily intended for
batch jobs and one-off scripts. This package is a fork of the project
once developed by Ole Martin Bjørndalen, and includes some additional
functionality.

name: catalystcoop.dbfread
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "catalystcoop.dbfread" %}
{% set version = "3.0.0" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.org/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: e79dc93ec2e5e4dc4f9a8daac2edc5b411026301fc80bd6ceb41b453d9c7ea36

build:
  noarch: python
  number: 1
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv"

requirements:
  host:
    - python {{ python_min }}
    - pip
    - setuptools
  run:
    - python >={{ python_min }}

test:
  imports:
    - dbfread
  source_files:
    - tests/
    - testcases/
  requires:
    - zipp
    - pytest
    - python {{ python_min }}
  commands:
    - pytest tests
    - dbf2sqlite --help

about:
  home: https://github.com/catalyst-cooperative/dbfread
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: "Read DBF files with Python."

  description: |
      DBF is a file format used by databases such dBase, Visual FoxPro, and
      FoxBase+. This library reads DBF files and returns the data as native
      Python data types for further processing. It is primarily intended for
      batch jobs and one-off scripts. This package is a fork of the project
      once developed by Ole Martin Bjørndalen, and includes some additional
      functionality.

  dev_url: https://github.com/catalyst-cooperative/dbfread

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - zaneselvans
